data.title: Real Housewives Of Atlanta: Drew Sidora cries when asked by producer about relationship with WNBA player after husband Ralph Pittman filed for divorce
data.meta_description: Drew Sidora, 38, cried when asked her about her relationship with WNBA basketball player Tamera 'Ty' Young on Sunday's episode of The Real Housewives of Atlanta.
data.text:
Drew Sidora cried when asked her about her relationship with WNBA basketball player Tamera 'Ty' Young on Sunday's episode of The Real Housewives of Atlanta.

A producer of the Bravo show questioned Drew, 38, in a confessional about her relationship with Ty and asked if they were just friends when Drew started crying.

Drew's confessional came after it was announced that her husband Ralph Pittman had filed for divorce. Marlo Hampton, 47, and the other housewives were shocked.

'I literally cannot believe it,' Sanya Richards-Ross, 38, said when she heard the news.

'Now what the streets are saying is she's dating Ty, top story baby,' Marlo said.

Drew said in a confessional before the divorce news broke that she had never kissed a woman. Courtney said, though, that Ralph believed Drew did kiss former friend of a housewife cast member LaToya Ali, 36,

'I mean, he just said that it was no secret,' Courtney Rhodes, 48, said.

When the season 15 episode titled Make Ups, Slip Ups and Cover Ups opened, Drew was crying outside of the restaurant during the first night of the girls trip in Portugal about how she was so upset because she was being sued by a former chef for $1,000.

Kandi Burruss, 47, thought she was being dramatic and acting.

'And scene,' Kandi said when Drew walked out.

'I have never been sued a day in my life,' Drew said. 'It's not funny to me.'

Sheree Whitfield, 53, went outside to talk to Drew, but Drew insisted she needed a moment.

'All the dramatics, I can't take it,' Sheree said in a confessional. 'Drew has come to me about things she's heard online about me. So don't expect to dish it, if you can't take it. Cause everything I hear, I'm bringing back to you, b****.'

Drew said in a confessional that the woman suing her had reached out to bloggers and her family to disrespect her.

'If there are any issues going on with her it must be about Ralph and their relationship,' Kenya Moore, 52, said in a confessional.

'I mean, she don't have $1,000?' Sheree said in a confessional.

'We can make it go away,' Kenya said. 'You need a better lawyer.'

A producer asked Drew if there was something she was not telling the other women.

Drew said when she went out of town last year was when the massage incident with the manager woman and Ralph happened. She said also at their recent video shoot one of the producers was oiling Ralph's chest and she was the one who invited him to go to Las Vegas.

'So now he's in Vegas and I'm just not really trusting him at this point,' Drew said.

The next morning, Sheree organized for them to go to a market and then to make pottery. The women all waited in a van for Kenya who finally walked outside and slipped on the wet pavement and fell on her butt.

'Oh, my back,' Kenya said.

Production helped her stand up and Kenya was crying.

'Please don't move me,' Kenya said.

Kenya said in a confessional that she felt excruciating pain coming from her back.

She was then shown being driven away in an ambulance to the hospital.

'Everything that can go wrong on this trip seems like it's going wrong,' Sheree said in a confessional. 'The weather is horrible. Kenya just fell. This is not the trip that I had planned.'

'I think we all deal with karma,' Courtney Rhodes, 48, said. 'She is a mean girl. That's how karma works, right?'

The ambulance took Kenya to the hospital and Kandi Burruss went with her. It was raining outside and the women were not happy.

They went to a food market and picked out food for a chef to cook for them for dinner. They saw a dead rabbit and said it had a BBL, Brazilian butt lift.

Kenya was still in the waiting room of the hospital on a stretcher. The women discussed how Kenya was blending in and not letting people know she was a VIP. They then went to lunch.

Monyetta Shaw, 43, called out Marlo for saying that she went on a date with Kenya's boyfriend Roi. In a confessional, Sheree said she didn't like Monyetta's double standards and 'a** kissing.'

'Monyetta, pull your head out of Kandi and Kenya's a**,' Sheree said in a confessional.

Sheree's boyfriend Martell called and told her to make sure that she thinks about him at night.

'Any man with a pulse and no ankle bracelet is an upgrade from Tyrone,' Marlo said in a confessional.

Drew said at the lunch that she wanted friends who cared about what she was dealing with in her life. Sheree pointed out that when Drew stormed out at dinner that Kandi said 'and scene' meaning that she thought Drew was just acting. Drew didn't seem to get upset by that.

After 7.5 hours, Kenya finally left the hospital.

'I do not have any broken bones,' Kenya said. 'I am alive, and well, and able to talk about my experience.'

Kandi and Kenya went back to the hotel to get some rest.

The rest of the women went to a pottery studio to paint pieces.

'Whenever Kenya and Kandi are not around, all of us get along,' Marlo said in a confessional. 'The energy is different.'

Sheree said they were going to have a slumber party when they went back to the hotel and ordered food to the room.

Drew confronted Kandi about how it was brought to her attention when she got up at the dinner and she said 'and scene.'

'It was a real moment,' Drew said.

'You'll wasn't even having that serious of an argument,' Kandi said.

'She thought it was fun shade,' Courtney said.

'It's a time for fun shade,' Drew said. 'It's a time to laugh. It's a time to have real conversations, a time to go at it. And then it's a time for me, which I have never experienced in front of this group, just me being vulnerable, and my immediate response was to run out.'

Kandi said she has seen Drew go back and forth with a lot of women in the group.

'Did it ever occur to you maybe because I've been dealing with something,' Drew said.

Drew said she was hurt by what Kandi said. Kandi said it was just a joke. Sanya got emotional talking about the strain between her and her sister.

Sheree then pointed out that no one had ordered anything off her website She by Sheree.

'I've got to keep asking you all to support me,' Sheree said.

The women all started dancing. Production wrapped at close to midnight. One hour later, Marlo continued to film reminiscing about their past Bolo trip when someone said that Drew made out with LaToya on that trip. Drew said it wasn't true even though LaToya said it was at the reunion.

'I said you cheated on your husband with me,' LaToya had said at the reunion.

'Girl you are not going to make me unsee what I saw,' Kandi said in a confessional.

Kandi got upset and said she wasn't lying and didn't like being called a liar and went to her room.

Drew said in a confessional that she had never kissed a woman.

The show ended with a To Be Continued message.

The Real Housewives of Atlanta will return next Sunday on Bravo.
